Sentencas: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers (CGCLs) of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-delta-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 (BSFA-GDC) have been constructed by a handy and effective technique called wet powder spraying (WPS).
Titulo: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 by wet powder spraying technique for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: CGCLs exhibit similar thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) value between adjacent thin layers.
Titulo: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 by wet powder spraying technique for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The continuously graded structure and the well-distributed components of BSFA-GDC cathode are confirmed by morphological characterization with scanning electron microscopy (SEM), and by compositional analysis with energy dispersion X-ray spectrometer (EDS), respectively.
Titulo: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 by wet powder spraying technique for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The polarization resistance (R-p) of CGCLs with three different thicknesses is investigated by electrochemical impedance spectra (EIS).
Titulo: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 by wet powder spraying technique for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The EIS results show that CGCLs with a moderate thickness of 20 mu m achieve the lowest R-p of 0.301 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 by wet powder spraying technique for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition, anode-supported single cells with the configuration of NiO-YSZ/YSZ/GDC/BSFA-GDC have been fabricated and tested.
Titulo: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 by wet powder spraying technique for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cell with the CGCLs thickness of 20 mu m reaches the highest output power density of 848 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. (C) 2013
Titulo: Compositionally continuously graded cathode layers of (Ba0.5Sr0.5)(Fe0.91Al0.09)O3-δ-Gd0.1Ce0.9O2 by wet powder spraying technique for solid oxide fuel cells
